Business Brief -- Bank of Boston Corp.:
   Firm Says It Plans to Sell
   Eight Million of Its Shares
Like most other New England banks, Bank of Boston recorded
losses because of the deep real estate slump and general
recession, but it returned to profitability in the second
half of 1991.
   Bank of Boston said in its filing with the Securities and
Exchange Commission that proceeds of the offering, managed by
Merrill Lynch  Co., will be added to the company's general
fund and used for corporate purposes. Bank of Boston
currently has 75.4 million common shares outstanding.